      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WYNBURN COBBER (7) drew a middle box and finished towards the tailenders on debut at this track over 461m (26.59). This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. TAKE OFF TWIGGY (1) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when sixth at this track over 340m behind Wynburn Elsey (20.38) in a Grade 6. Has ability and can measure up. IRISHTOWN (4) shows ability but remains a maiden after six starts. Was below best latest when fourth (30.63) at Launceston but did hit the frame the start prior. Has ability and can atone. CRACKERJACK OAK (2) jumps at a shorter journey and still warrants respect.",
